sp.p:
We have been five Weeks in Priſon: 'Tis meet the Court
ſhould know for what. Pray let our Mittimus be produced, and read in Court;
that it may be underſtood what Charge we ſuffer under.

They are no Fictions: Pray read them, or let them be read;
they are from Perſons of Credit and Repute, as Common-Council men, Deputy
Conſtables, Church-Wardens, and others.

It may be a Proteſtation or Teſtimony againſt Popery;

yet not an Oath. I pray you, let's read our Proteſtation,
that we may not lie under Suſpition, without cauſe.

